cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the generalization properties of stochastic gradient methods for learning with convex loss functions and linearly parameterized functions. This topic is closely related to machine learning and optimization, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it directly deals with learning and generalization. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also likely categories as they often involve optimization and machine learning techniques. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are less likely but still possible categories as they also involve optimization and machine learning techniques.
